This article looks at both the technical and political economy aspects of fiscal and monetary policy to understand how and why this transformation took place.
 It is argued that the use of monetary policy as the principal instrument to control inflation,
 is technically flawed while the experience of monetary policy over the past 30 or so years shows how the political economy issues that led to the decline of fiscal policy as the main instrument of demand management can now be overcome,
 so as to achieve effective macroeconomic management,
